Method Detail

getKam

Kam getKam(String handleOrName)
Retrieves a Kam by its handle (in the case of a cached KAM). If no Kam is found by handle, this method attempts to find a Kam by name.

Parameters:
handleOrName - String handle or Kam name
Returns:
Kam; may be null

loadKam

String loadKam(KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo ki,
               KAMCatalogDao.KamFilter kf)
               throws KamCacheServiceException
Loads a Kam by KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo, returning a handle to it. This method blocks while the Kam is loaded.

Parameters:
ki - KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo
kf - KAMCatalogDao.KamFilter used to filter the edges and Kam.KamNode nodes before loading
Returns:
String The Kam handle
Throws:
KamCacheServiceException - TODO Document why this exception is thrown.

loadKamWithResult

KamCacheService.LoadKAMResult loadKamWithResult(KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo ki,
                                                KAMCatalogDao.KamFilter kf)
                                                throws KamCacheServiceException
Loads a Kam by KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo, returning a handle to it. This method will not block and can be used to poll the service until the Kam is available.

Parameters:
kamInfo - KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo
kamFilter - KAMCatalogDao.KamFilter used to filter the edges and Kam.KamNode nodes before loading
Returns:
KamCacheService.LoadKAMResult
Throws:
KamCacheServiceException

cacheKam

String cacheKam(String name,
                Kam kam)
Cache the Kam returning a handle associated with the provided name. If name is null, the Kam will be cached by the KamInfo KAMCatalogDao.KamInfo.getName().

Parameters:
name - String to cache the Kam by; may be null
kam - Kam, the kam to cache
Returns:
String The Kam handle
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if a KAM name was not provided and none was available in the kam argument
See Also:
getKam - Retrieving a KAM by handle

Throws:
